ins an intact\nintrauterine gestational sac, yolk sac and fetal pole.  The crown\nrump length measures 1.2 cm which corresponds to a gestational age\nof 7 weeks and 3 days.  The fetal heart rate measures 157\nbeats/min.  Estimated date of delivery is <redacted>.\nThere is tiny inferior subchorionic bleed.\n\nThe cervix is closed.  There is trace free fluid in the\ncul-de-sac.\n\nThe right ovary is normal in echotexture and size, measuring 2.4 x\n2.1 x 1.9 cm.  There is a normal follicular pattern and color\nDoppler flow.\n\nThe left ovary is only identified on the trans-abdominal images,\nand is normal in echotexture and size, measuring 3.3 x 1.8 x 1.4\ncm.  There is a normal follicular pattern and color Doppler flow.\n\nIMPRESSION:\n\n1. Intact intrauterine pregnancy.  Estimated gestation age of 7\nweeks and 3 days.  Fetal heart rate of 157 beats/min.  Estimated\ndate of delivery is <redacted>.\n\n2. Trace free fluid within the cul-de-sac.\n\nEND OF IMPRESSION:\n\n\nI have personally reviewed the image(s) and this original or edited\nreport represents my interpretation.\n'),(9,'90','CROSSMAN^MANUEL^^^','1990-02-20','F','9','F','ACU1','Pelvic Pain','US OB TRANSVAGINAL EXAM  76817','P16898','SON219','O','SONO','UM','ANYTECH',NULL,'DOCTOR, MD','39','15','INDICATION:  Pelvic pain status post fall.\n\nTECHNIQUE:  Real time gray scale and color Doppler ultrasonography\nof the pelvis was performed via transabdominal and endovaginal\nimaging.\n\nCOMPARISON:  None.\n\nFINDINGS:  Transabdominal: The uterus is anteverted, and contains\nan intact uterine gestational sac.\n\nTransvaginal imaging was subsequently performed for further\nevaluation.\n\nTransvaginal:    The uterus is anteverted and contains an intact\nintrauterine gestational sac, yolk sac and fetal pole.  The crown\nrump length measures 1.2 cm which corresponds to a gestational age\nof 7 weeks and 3 days.  The fetal heart rate measures 157\nbeats/min.  Estimated date of delivery is <redacted>.\nThere is tiny inferior subchorionic bleed.\n\nThe cervix is closed.  There is trace free fluid in the\ncul-de-sac.\n\nThe right ovary is normal in echotexture and size, measuring 2.4 x\n2.1 x 1.9 cm.  There is a normal follicular pattern and color\nDoppler flow.\n\nThe left ovary is only identified on the trans-abdominal images,\nand is normal in echotexture and size, measuring 3.3 x 1.8 x 1.4\ncm.  There is a normal follicular pattern and color Doppler flow.\n\nIMPRESSION:\n\n1. Intact intrauterine pregnancy.  Estimated gestation age of 7\nweeks and 3 days.  Fetal heart rate of 157 beats/min.  Estimated\ndate of delivery is <redacted>.\n\n2. Trace free fluid within the cul-de-sac.\n\nEND OF IMPRESSION:\n\nI have personally reviewed the image(s) and this original or edited\nreport represents my interpretation.\n'),(10,'1','COURAGE^SEAMUS^^^','1990-02-20','F','10','F','SWISS1','Dehydration','CHEST 2VWS PA/LATERAL    71020','P25696','EXR45','O','EXR','UM','ANYTECH',NULL,'DOCTOR, MD','40','6','INDICATION:  Wheezing, cough, and yellow sputum.  Currently on\nantibiotics.\n\nCOMPARISON: None.\n\nFINDINGS:\n\nPA and lateral views of the chest demonstrate no focal\nconsolidation or atelectasis.  There are streaky opacities\noverlying the left lung base on the frontal view this is not\nconfirmed on the lateral view. There is no evidence of pleural\ndisease. The cardiomediastinal silhouette is unremarkable.   The\nvisualized abdomen and regional skeletal structures are\nunremarkable.\n\nI have personally reviewed the image(s) and this original or edited\nreport represents my interpretation.\n'),(11,'110','LEFERTINI^EMELIA^^^','1990-02-20','F','11','P','TRCT1','Intracranial Hemorrhage','CTA BRAIN                70496','P27734','NCT131','I','CT','UM','ANYTECH',NULL,'DOCTOR, MD','45','15','INDICATION: Intracranial hemorrhage.\n\nTECHNIQUE:Contiguous 5 mm transverse scans were obtained\nprecontrast followed by brain CTA protocol after intravenous\ninjection of iodinated contrast.  2-D multiplanar reformatted\nreconstructions were performed.\n\nFINDINGS:\n\nNoncontrast CT of the brain demonstrates a right frontal hematoma\nextending to the basal ganglia and parietal lobes measuring\napproximately 4 0.3 x 4.0 x 3.6 cm with surrounding hypodensity.\nThere is midline shift to the left measuring approximately 1.0 cm\nwith effacement of the right lateral ventricle.  Chronic left\ncerebellar infarct is identified.  An endotracheal and nasogastric\ntubes are seen coursing through the oropharynx.  There is mild\nposterior ethmoid air cell and sphenoid sinus opacification.  The\nmastoid air cells are clear.\n\nCT angiography of the head is limited due to suboptimal contrast\nbolus.  There is no evidence of an aneurysm or arteriovenous\nmalformation.  A small vascular lesion may be partially obscured\nby the large right frontal hematoma. There is calcification of the\ncavernous segment of the right internal carotid artery with\nnarrowing that is felt to be accentuated by calcification. There\nis mild irregularity of the basilar artery.  There is no evidence\nof occlusion or hemodynamically significant stenosis of the distal\nbranches of the circle of Willis.  Note is made of a left fetal\nPCA. The source images showed no evidence of aneurysm at the major\nvascular bifurcations.\n\nThere is no evidence of stenosis at the carotid bifurcations.\nThere is a lucency over the second molar of the right mandible\nthat is concerning for a periapical abscess formation.\n\n\nIMPRESSION:\n1.  Large right frontal hematoma extending to the basal ganglia\nand parietal lobes with midline shift and effacement of the right\nlateral ventricle.\n2.  No evidence of aneurysm arteriovenous malformation however, a\nsmall vascular lesion that is partially obscured by the large\nright hematoma cannot be ruled out.\n3.  Questionable right mandibular periapical abscess of the second\nmolar.  Clinical correlation is recommended.\n'),(12,'21','AIOLAS^ARVEL^^^','1990-02-20','M','12','F','ORTHO1','L-spine','LUMBAR SPINE 2/3 VIEWS   72100','P18596','EXR114','O','EXR','UM','ANYTECH',NULL,'DOCTOR, MD','47','4','INDICATION: Lower back pain.\n\nL-SPINE: Two views of the L-spine are provided with no prior\navailable for comparison.  There is minimal joint space narrowing\nat the L5-S1 junction with mild sclerosis of the endplates.  There\nis minimal anterolisthesis of L5 on S1, with probable L5 pars\ndefects. Contrast within the bowel obscures evaluation of much of\nthe L3, L4, and L5 vertebral bodies. Alignment is otherwise\nmaintained.\n\nI have personally reviewed the image(s) and this original or edited\nreport represents my interpretation.\n'),(13,'31','HARRISON^GEORGE^^^','1990-02-20','M','13','F','SWISS1','Suspected fracture','HAND MIN 3 VIEWS         73130','P27720','EXR280','O','EXR','UM','ANYTECH',NULL,'DOCTOR, MD','36','4','Diagnosis:\nSuspected fracture.\n\nFindings:\nLeft hand in three views.\n.\nThere is no evidence of fracture or dislocation.  Lytic lesions\nare not identified.\n\nImpression:\nNo evidence of bony lesion.\n'),(14,'41','JAYLIN^BEATA^^^','1990-02-20','F','14','F','SWISS1','Trauma with Pain and Swelling','KNEE 1 OR 2 VIEWS        73560','P25696','EXR140','O','EXR','UM','ANYTECH',NULL,'DOCTOR, MD','55','5','INDICATION: Trauma with left knee pain and swelling.\n\nCOMPARISON: None available.\n\nFINDINGS: Two views of the left knee demonstrate no acute fracture\nor dislocation.  There is 1.4 cm suprapatellar capsular distention\ncompatible with a joint effusion.  No evidence of\nlipohemarthrosis.\n\nIf there is concern for occult fracture or internal derangement,\nMRI might be considered.\n\nI have personally reviewed the image(s) and this original or edited\nreport represents my interpretation.\n'),(15,'51','GIAMATTI^TONI^^^','1990-02-20','F','15','F','AMBER','EVALUATE FOR HIRSHSPRUNG\'S DZ','BARIUM ENEMA             74270','P25423','XRA210','O','XRA','UM','ANYTECH',NULL,'DOCTOR, MD','42','5','INDICATION: Chronic constipation.\n\nIMPRESSION: Normal contrast enema.\n\nCOMMENT: The preliminary AP view of the abdomen is unremarkable.\nNo excess of stool is suggested.\n\nFollowing the transrectal catheter placement and taping, Omnipaque\nwater siphon contrast was hand injected into the rectum under\nfluoroscopic monitoring, followed by serial spot filming.  The\nrectum and entire colon appears structurally normal with no\ntransition zone to suggest Hirschsprung\'s disease and no evidence\nof malrotation, stricture, or other colonic abnormality.  Overall,\nthe study is within normal limits.\n'),(16,'61','NANNY^LINDSAY^^^','1990-02-20','F','16','F','ACU1','THYROID NODULES ','US FNA             10022/76942','P14789','SON533','O','SONO','UM','ANYTECH',NULL,'DOCTOR, MD','56','20','Indication: Bilateral thyroid nodules\n\nTechnique:  Grayscale and color Doppler ultrasound of the thyroid\ngland was performed.\n\nComparison: Report from ultrasound dated 9/16/08 performed at\nadvanced radiology services.  Images not available for direct\ncomparison.\n\nFindings:\nThe right lobe measures 2.2 x 1.2 x 4.3 cm.  There is a lobular\nhypoechoic nodule in the posterior lower pole measuring 2.0 x 0.8\nx 1.7 cm.  This appears predominantly cystic with a thickened\nwall.  There is some internal flow.  On the prior study this was\nmeasured as 1.9 x 1.1 x 1.5 cm. There is a small amount of solid\nnodule in the lateral right midpole measuring 0.7 x 0.4 x 0.8 cm.\n\nThe left lobe measures 1.5 x 1.1 x 4.3 cm.  There is a\npredominantly solid nodule in the posterior midpole which contains\ninternal calcifications, this measures 1.3 x 0.9 x 1.0 cm.  On the\nprior study this measured 1.7 x 0.9 x 1.0 cm.  No additional\nnodules are identified in the left lobe.  The isthmus measures 2\nmm in thickness.\n\nFNA: Informed written consent was obtained from the patient\nfollowing an explanation of the procedure, its indications,\nalternatives and risks.  Time out procedure was performed prior to\nthe procedure to confirm patient identity.  The anterior neck was\nprepped and draped in routine sterile fashion.  Starting with the\nright lobe, the skin and subcutaneous tissues were anesthetized\nwith 1% lidocaine, and 4 passes with 25-gauge needles were made\ninto the lower pole nodule.  Specimens were submitted to the\npathologist on site who deemed the sample adequate.  Next the left\nlobe was targeted, skin and subcutaneous tissues anesthetized with\n1% lidocaine.  Three passes with 25-gauge needles were made into\nthe midpole nodule.  Specimen was deemed adequate by the on-site\npathologist.\n\nThere were no immediate complications.\n\n\nIMPRESSION:\n\n1.  Predominantly cystic hypoechoic nodule in the posterior lower\npole of the right lobe of the thyroid gland.  This measures\nsimilar in size to the recent comparison study reported.  There is\na smaller lateral midpole nodule not previously mentioned.\n\n2.  Solitary predominantly solid nodule in the left lobe of the\nthyroid gland, similar in size to the report from the prior study.\n\n3.  Fine needle aspiration of the two largest nodules as detailed\nabove.\n\n\n\nEND OF IMPRESSION:\n\nI have personally reviewed the image(s) and this original or edited\nreport represents my interpretation.\n'),(19,'91','GIULIO^WILBUR^^^','1990-02-20','M','19','F','TRCT2','Other','TR CT BRAIN W/O CONTRAST 70450','P29929','NCT366','I','CT','UM','ANYTECH',NULL,'DOCTOR, MD','48','13','INDICATION: MVC, unrestrained.\n\nHEAD CT: Unenhanced multi-detector scanning was performed.\n\nCOMPARISON: None.\n\nThe brain parenchyma is normal.\n\nThere is no hemorrhage, shift, hydrocephalus, or calvarial\nfracture.\n\nLeft frontal scalp contusion\n\nIMPRESSION:\n\n1.  No evidence of acute intracranial injury.\n\n\n\nFACE CT:  Helical multi-detector scanning was performed. Coronal\nreconstructed images were created.\n\nThe paranasal sinuses are well aerated.\n\nThe bones and orbits are normal.\n\nThere is a left sided fracture in the proximal aspect of the body\nof the mandible. Fracture in the ventral aspect of the right\nmandible  close to the symphysis.\n\nIMPRESSION:\n\nBilateral mandible fractures.\n\n\n\nEND OF IMPRESSION:\n\n\n'),(21,'12','SHERWOOD^RAY^^^','1990-02-20','M','21','F','TRAC 1','pain','TR AP CHEST PORTABLE     71010','P21979','MXR701','I','MXR','UM','ANYTECH',NULL,'DOCTOR, MD','57','4','Indication: Pain\n\nPortable chest in one view\n\nFindings:\nSharp delineated hemi-diaphragm bilateral. Unremarkable silhouette\nof the heart and mediastinum. Symmetrically aerated  lungs without\nevidence of infiltrate, effusion or pneumothorax. No evidence of\ndislocated rib fractures.\n\nImpression:\nNo evidence of acute pulmonary pathologies.\n'),(22,'220','ROMANO^CESAR^^^','1990-02-20','M','22','F','TRAC 1','pain','TR PELVIS 1 OR 2 VIEWS   72170','P21979','MXR120','I','MXR','UM','ANYTECH',NULL,'DOCTOR, MD','52','4','INDICATION: Status post MVC, now with pelvic pain.\n\nPELVIS: Single AP view of the pelvis is provided with no prior\navailable for comparison.  There is a small calcific density just\nmedial to the lesser trochanter of the right femur.  This is may\nrepresent a tiny avulsion fracture or debris external to the\npatient.  No other evidence of fracture or dislocation, however\ncontrast within the bladder obscures optimal evaluation of the\nsuperior pubic rami.\n\nI have personally reviewed the image(s) and this original or edited\nreport represents my interpretation.\n'),(23,'32','JENSEN^ANNABELLA^^^','1990-02-20','F','23','F','TSRM1','RIGHT KNEE PAIN','KNEE MIN 4 VIEWS','P24358','73564','O','TSORTH','TS','ANYTECH',NULL,'DOCTOR, MD','51','4','INDICATION: Right knee pain.\n\nRIGHT KNEE: 4 views of the right knee are provided with no prior\navailable for comparison.  There is moderate tricompartmental\njoint space narrowing with osteophyte formation, most notable\nalong the superior and medial aspects of the patella.  There is no\nevidence of fracture or dislocation.\n\nI have personally reviewed the image(s) and this original or 